Package com.rb.biz.investing.modeling.selection.overrides

Class BehaviorWithValueAndOverride<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>

java.lang.Object
com.rb.biz.investing.modeling.selection.overrides.BehaviorWithValueAndOverride<T>
Direct Known Subclasses:
BehaviorWithValueAndOverride.AlwaysUseExistingValueAndIgnoreOverride, BehaviorWithValueAndOverride.AlwaysUseOverrideAndIgnoreExistingValue, BehaviorWithValueAndOverride.OnlyUseOverrideToFurtherReduceExistingValue
public abstract class BehaviorWithValueAndOverride<T extends java.lang.Comparable<? super T>>
extends java.lang.Object
Describes what we should do in cases where there is both a value and an override.

The 3 different method names are self-explanatory about what they do. The option to 'further reduce' is the least obvious one. Here is an example. Our backtesting code (not part of this repo) supports 3 modes for any instrument in the backtest: untradable; only sellable; freely tradable. Note that the generic class T implements Comparable, so there is a requirement for ordering here.

Say that the default value is specified as 'untradable'. If an override says 'AAPL is freely tradable', then AAPL should be 'freely tradable'. If an override says 'XYZ is untradable', then XYZ will be 'only sellable'.

See Also:
BehaviorWithValueButNoOverride, Overrides, OverridesApplier
